{\n  "nbformat": 4,\n  "nbformat_minor": 5,\n  "metadata": {\n    "kernelspec": {\n      "display_name": "Python 3",\n      "language": "python",\n      "name": "python3"\n    },\n    "language_info": {\n      "name": "python",\n      "version": "3.11"\n    }\n  },\n  "cells": [\n    {\n      "cell_type": "markdown",\n      "metadata": {},\n      "source": [\n        "# SI-QBER — Entropy vs QBER Analysis\n",\n        "\n",\n        "This notebook runs multiple simulation trials across an entropy schedule and summarizes how observed QBER responds as entropy increases or decreases. It uses the same storage-corruption model used earlier (exponential coherence decay + entropy-scaled thermal noise).\n",\n        "\n",\n        "Outputs:\n",\n        "- Mean and standard deviation of observed QBER per entropy level\n",\n        "- Plots showing QBER vs entropy and p_error vs entropy\n",\n        "- CSV export of aggregated results\n",\n        "\n",\n        "Usage: run all cells. Install dependencies if necessary (numpy, matplotlib, pandas).\n"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      "cell_type": "code",\n      "metadata": {},\n      "source": [\n        "import math\n",\n        "import numpy as np\n",\n        "import pandas as pd\n",\n        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",\n        "from datetime import datetime\n",\n        "import os\n",\n        "\n",\n        "np.random.seed(42)\n",\n        "RESULTS_DIR = \"entropy_analysis_results\"\n",\n        "os.makedirs(RESULTS_DIR, exist_ok=True)\n"\n      ],\n      "execution_count": null,\n      "outputs": []\n    },\n    {\n      "cell_type": "markdown",\n      "metadata": {},\n      "source": [\n        "## Inject storage corruption function\n",\n        "Re-implemented here for self-contained analysis (identical behavior to the script provided earlier)."\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      "cell_type": "code",\n      "metadata": {},\n      "source": [\n        "def inject_storage_corruption(bits, cycles, T2=25.0, base_error_rate=0.02, entropy=0.0, thermal_scale=0.05):\n",\n        "    \"\"\"\n",\n        "    bits: 1D numpy array of 0/1\n",\n        "    cycles: scalar (number of storage cycles)\n",\n        "    T2: coherence time in cycles\n",\n        "    base_error_rate: baseline hardware/readout error\n",\n        "    entropy: additional noise factor (>=0)\n",\n        "    thermal_scale: scales entropy contribution\n",\n        "    Returns: (corrupted_bits, p_error, observed_qber)\n",\n        "    \"\"\"\n",\n        "    n = len(bits)\n",\n        "    p_error = 1.0 - math.exp(-float(cycles) / float(T2))\n",\n        "    corrupted = bits.copy()\n",\n        "    positions = np.linspace(0.0, 1.0, n)\n",\n        "    for i in range(n):\n",\n        "        # flip probability combines base error, position-weighted physical p_error, and entropy-driven noise\n",\n        "        flip_prob = base_error_rate + p_error * positions[i] + entropy * thermal_scale * np.random.random()\n",\n        "        if np.random.random() < flip_prob:\n",\n        "            corrupted[i] = 1 - corrupted[i]\n",\n        "    qber = float(np.sum(corrupted != bits)) / float(n)\n",\n        "    return corrupted, p_error, qber\n"\n      ],\n      "execution_count": null,\n      "outputs": []\n    },\n    {\n      "cell_type": "markdown",\n      "metadata": {},\n      "source": [\n        "## Batch experiment function\n",\n        "Runs multiple independent trials per entropy level and aggregates mean/std of observed QBER and p_error."\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      "cell_type": "code",\n      "metadata": {},\n      "source": [\n        "def run_entropy_experiment(mode='increase',\n",\n        "                         entropy_values=None,\n",\n        "                         cycles=50,\n",\n        "                         nbits=2048,\n",\n        "                         trials_per_entropy=50,\n",\n        "                         T2=25.0,\n",\n        "                         base_error_rate=0.02,\n",\n        "                         thermal_scale=0.05,\n",\n        "                         seed=None):\n",\n        "    \"\"\"\n",\n        "    mode: 'increase' or 'decrease' (affects ordering only)\n",\n        "    entropy_values: iterable of entropy values to test (if None, uses np.linspace(0,1,21))\n",\n        "    cycles: storage cycles used for each trial (scalar or iterable length match entropy_values)\n",\n        "    trials_per_entropy: independent random trials per entropy value\n",\n        "    Returns: pandas.DataFrame with aggregated results\n",\n        "    \"\"\"\n",\n        "    if entropy_values is None:\n",\n        "        entropy_values = np.linspace(0.0, 1.0, 21)\n",\n        "    entropy_values = np.array(entropy_values)\n",\n        "    if mode == 'decrease':\n",\n        "        entropy_values = entropy_values[::-1]\n",\n        "    records = []\n",\n        "    base_seed = int(seed) if seed is not None else None\n",\n        "    for idx, ent in enumerate(entropy_values):\n",\n        "        # allow cycles to be scalar or an array-like per-entropy\n",\n        "        cyc = cycles[idx] if hasattr(cycles, '__len__') and len(cycles) == len(entropy_values) else cycles\n",\n        "        qber_vals = []\n",\n        "        p_error_vals = []\n",\n        "        for t in range(trials_per_entropy):\n",\n        "            if base_seed is not None:\n",\n        "                # vary the seed deterministically per trial\n",\n        "                np.random.seed(base_seed + idx * trials_per_entropy + t)\n",\n        "            bits = np.random.randint(0, 2, size=nbits, dtype=np.uint8)\n",\n        "            _, p_error, qber = inject_storage_corruption(bits, cycles=cyc, T2=T2,\n",\n        "                                                        base_error_rate=base_error_rate,\n",\n        "                                                        entropy=float(ent),\n",\n        "                                                        thermal_scale=float(thermal_scale))\n",\n        "            qber_vals.append(qber)\n",\n        "            p_error_vals.append(p_error)\n",\n        "        records.append({\n",\n        "            'entropy': float(ent),\n",\n        "            'cycles': int(cyc),\n",\n        "            'qber_mean': float(np.mean(qber_vals)),\n",\n        "            'qber_std': float(np.std(qber_vals, ddof=1)),\n",\n        "            'p_error_mean': float(np.mean(p_error_vals)),\n",\n        "            'p_error_std': float(np.std(p_error_vals, ddof=1)),\n",\n        "            'trials': int(trials_per_entropy)\n",\n        "        })\n",\n        "    df = pd.DataFrame.from_records(records)\n",\n        "    return df\n"\n      ],\n      "execution_count": null,\n      "outputs": []\n    },\n    {\n      "cell_type": "markdown",\n      "metadata": {},\n      "source": [\n        "## Run experiments (example)\n",\n        "Adjust parameters below for resolution, number of trials, cycles, etc. This example uses a modest number of trials to keep runtime short."\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      "cell_type": "code",\n      "metadata": {},\n      "source": [\n        "# Parameters (tweak for more resolution / confidence)\n",\n        "MODE = 'increase'            # 'increase' or 'decrease'\n",\n        "ENTROPY_VALUES = np.linspace(0.0, 1.0, 21)\n",\n        "CYCLES = 40                 # can be scalar or array of same length as ENTROPY_VALUES\n",\n        "NBITS = 4096\n",\n        "TRIALS_PER_ENTROPY = 80     # increase for tighter CI\n",\n        "T2 = 25.0\n",\n        "BASE_ERROR = 0.02\n",\n        "THERMAL_SCALE = 0.05\n",\n        "SEED = 12345\n",\n        "\n",\n        "df = run_entropy_experiment(mode=MODE,\n",\n        "                            entropy_values=ENTROPY_VALUES,\n",\n        "                            cycles=CYCLES,\n",\n        "                            nbits=NBITS,\n",\n        "                            trials_per_entropy=TRIALS_PER_ENTROPY,\n",\n        "                            T2=T2,\n",\n        "                            base_error_rate=BASE_ERROR,\n",\n        "                            thermal_scale=THERMAL_SCALE,\n",\n        "                            seed=SEED)\n",\n        "\n",\n        "print(df.head())\n",\n        "csv_path = os.path.join(RESULTS_DIR, f\"entropy_experiment_{MODE}_{datetime.utcnow().strftime('%Y%m%dT%H%M%SZ')}.csv\")\n",\n        "df.to_csv(csv_path, index=False)\n",\n        "print('Saved CSV:', csv_path)\n"\n      ],\n      "execution_count": null,\n      "outputs": []\n    },\n    {\n      "cell_type": "markdown",\n      "metadata": {},\n      "source": [\n        "## Plot results\n",\n        "Plot mean QBER with error bars (std) and p_error trend."\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      "cell_type": "code",\n      "metadata": {},\n      "source": [\n        "fig, ax1 = plt.subplots(figsize=(8,5))\n",\n        "ax1.errorbar(df['entropy'], df['qber_mean'], yerr=df['qber_std'], fmt='-o', label='Observed QBER (mean ± std)', color='tab:blue')\n",\n        "ax1.set_xlabel('Entropy (arb. units)')\n",\n        "ax1.set_ylabel('Observed QBER', color='tab:blue')\n",\n        "ax1.tick_params(axis='y', labelcolor='tab:blue')\n",\n        "\n",\n        "ax2 = ax1.twinx()\n",\n        "ax2.plot(df['entropy'], df['p_error_mean'], '-s', color='tab:orange', label='Physical p_error (mean)')\n",\n        "ax2.set_ylabel('Physical p_error', color='tab:orange')\n",\n        "ax2.tick_params(axis='y', labelcolor='tab:orange')\n",\n        "\n",\n        "fig.suptitle('Entropy vs Observed QBER and Physical p_error')\n",\n        "ax1.grid(True, linestyle='--', alpha=0.4)\n",\n        "fig.tight_layout()\n",\n        "plt.show()\n"\n      ],\n      "execution_count": null,\n      "outputs": []\n    },\n    {\n      "cell_type": "markdown",\n      "metadata": {},\n      "source": [\n        "## Summary statistics and interpretation\n",\n        "Print a concise summary and highlight entropy levels where mean QBER crosses common viability thresholds (e.g., 0.11 = 11%)."\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      "cell_type": "code",\n      "metadata": {},\n      "source": [\n        "THRESHOLD = 0.11\n",\n        "above = df[df['qber_mean'] >= THRESHOLD]\n",\n        "if not above.empty:\n",\n        "    first_above = above.iloc[0]\n",\n        "    print(f\"Mean QBER exceeds {THRESHOLD:.3f} at entropy={first_above['entropy']:.3f} (mean={first_above['qber_mean']:.4f}, std={first_above['qber_std']:.4f})\")\n",\n        "else:\n",\n        "    print(f\"Mean QBER stays below {THRESHOLD:.3f} for tested entropy range.\")\n",\n        "\n",\n        "print('\nTop rows:')\n",\n        "display(df.head(10))\n"\n      ],\n      "execution_count": null,\n      "outputs": []\n    },\n    {\n      "cell_type": "markdown",\n      "metadata": {},\n      "source": [\n        "## Next steps / Extensions\n",\n        "- Replace the toy inject_storage_corruption with the repository's real function and confirm interfaces.\n",\n        "- Sweep cycles as well as entropy (2D grid) and visualize heatmaps of mean QBER.\n",\n        "- Use the trained SIQBERPredictor to correct observed QBER per-sample and measure Path Recovery as described in README.\n",\n        "- Export results and attach them to an artifact release (e.g., CSV + figures).\n"\n      ]\n    }\n  ]\n}